# Deploying to phonegentic.ai

The site runs an Axum (Rust) server on port 3000 behind nginx with TLS on `phonegentic.ai`.

## Key paths on the remote server

| What | Remote path |
|------|-------------|
| Static HTML/CSS/JS | `/var/html/` |
| Rust server source | `/root/phonegentic/static/static_server/` |
| Release binary | `/root/phonegentic/static/static_server/target/release/static_server` |
| systemd service | `static_server` (`/etc/systemd/system/static_server.service`) |

## Deploying static files (HTML, CSS, JS)

```bash
scp static/<file> root@phonegentic.ai:/var/html/
```

Do NOT deploy to `/var/www/html/` — the Axum server serves from `/var/html/`.

## Deploying Rust server changes

1. SCP source to the correct remote path:
```bash
scp static/static_server/src/main.rs root@phonegentic.ai:/root/phonegentic/static/static_server/src/main.rs
```

2. Build and restart (always source cargo env for non-interactive SSH):
```bash
ssh root@phonegentic.ai "source \$HOME/.cargo/env && cd /root/phonegentic/static/static_server && cargo build --release && systemctl restart static_server"
```

## Common mistakes to avoid

- **Wrong HTML path**: Files must go to `/var/html/`, not `/var/www/html/`
- **Wrong Rust source path**: Source goes to `/root/phonegentic/static/static_server/`, not `/root/static_server/`
- **Forgetting server-side**: API endpoints (like form handlers) have both client-side JS validation and server-side Rust validation — changes often need both
